results.name: Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of chains of length k in the partially ordered (by subspace inclusion) set of all subspaces of GF(2)^n, n>=0, 0<=k<=n.
link: Geoffrey Critzer, Combinatorics of Vector Spaces over Finite Fields, Master's thesis, Emporia State University, 2018.
formula: T(n,k)/A005329(n) is the coefficient of y^k*x^n in eq(x)^2/(1 - y (eq(x) - 1)) where eq(x) is the q-exponential function.
mathematica: nn}] CoefficientList[Series[ eq[z]^2/(1 - u (eq[z] - 1)) /. q -> 2, {z, 0, nn}], {z, u}]]]
xref: Cf. A289546, A293844 (row sums), A005329 (main diagonal), A006116 (column k = 0).
results.author: _Geoffrey Critzer_, Oct 17 2017
